=== SSN / PII HANDLING ANALYSIS ===

SSN HASHING (lib/security/ssn.ts):
- Uses SHA-256 with SSN_SALT from environment — GOOD
- No hardcoded fallback salt — GOOD
- Throws error if SSN_SALT missing — GOOD (fails safely)
- Stores ssn_hash + ssn_last4, never full SSN — GOOD

SSN ENCRYPTION (lib/security/ssn-helper.ts):
- Uses AES-256-CBC with SSN_ENCRYPTION_KEY from environment — GOOD
- Random IV per encryption — GOOD
- Throws error if key missing — GOOD
- Used for tax filing where SSN must be recoverable for IRS submission

SSN LOGGING:
- Zero instances of SSN values being logged — GOOD

FERPA AUDIT LOGGING:
- Audit log system exists (lib/auditLog.ts) — GOOD
- Only 1 of 17 SSN-handling routes has audit logging — HIGH RISK
- 16 SSN-handling routes have NO audit trail:
  - identity/verify-ssn — SSN verification with no audit
  - hr/payroll — payroll with SSN, no audit
  - supersonic-fast-cash/* — 6 tax routes with SSN, no audit
  - reports/wioa — WIOA reports with SSN, no audit
  - reports/rapids/export — RAPIDS export with SSN, no audit
  - franchise/clients — client data with SSN, no audit
  - tax/* — 3 tax routes with SSN, no audit
- Only 58 of 917 API routes (6.3%) have audit logging

PII AT REST:
- SSN: Hashed (SHA-256) or encrypted (AES-256-CBC) — GOOD
- DOB, address, email, phone: Stored in plaintext in Supabase — MEDIUM
  - Supabase provides disk encryption at rest
  - No column-level encryption for PII fields
  - Gov auditors may require column-level encryption for FERPA compliance

SEVERITY:
- HIGH: 16/17 SSN-handling routes lack audit logging (FERPA violation)
- HIGH: Only 6.3% of API routes have audit logging
- MEDIUM: PII fields (DOB, address, phone) stored without column-level encryption
